11/10/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Interior Minister Ivica Dacic announced Saturday (October 10th) that the country has issued arrest warrants for two people suspected of being involved in the murder of a French football fan in Belgrade. Brice Taton, 28, a fan of French football club Toulouse, died in hospital on September 28th, after he was attacked by fans of rival team Partizan Belgrade ahead of a match between the two squads. His death sparked a wave of protests in Serbia against violence, and President Boris Tadic vowed that the perpetrators will be arrested. (AFP, B92 - 10/10/09)
